DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/orbit?schema=public"
# Optional. Direct Postgres URL (non-pooled) for `prisma migrate` / `db` CLI
# when `DATABASE_URL` points at a pooler — avoids P1002 advisory lock
# timeouts on some hosts (e.g. PlanetScale psdb, port 6432). Not used at runtime
# by the API (see `readConfig` / `createPrismaClient`).
# DIRECT_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://…@…:5432/…?sslmode=verify-full"

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Background jobs
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# JOBS_PROVIDER selects the adapter for the `JobQueue` + `JobRuntime` ports.
# Leave unset (or set to "noop") to boot without background work —
# services that would have enqueued jobs will 409 from the noop adapter.
# Supported: "graphile" (self-hosted Postgres-backed), "qstash" (Upstash
# managed HTTP queue — serverless-friendly, no long-lived worker process).
# graphile-worker only ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional direct / session URL for graphile (LISTEN, NOTIFY, long-lived
# pool). If unset, the worker uses `DATABASE_URL` like the rest of the
# API. Use this when `DATABASE_URL` points at a transaction pooler that
# doesn't keep `LISTEN` sessions alive (e.g. PgBouncer in tx mode).
# Parallelism for this worker instance. Default: 2.
# QStash only ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Publish-side API token. Grab it from the Upstash QStash console.
# Current + next signing keys — QStash rotates keys, so both must be
# checked when verifying inbound webhook deliveries to /v1/jobs/run/:name.
# Publicly reachable base URL of this API. QStash delivers each job to
# `${QSTASH_CALLBACK_URL}/v1/jobs/run/<name>` — must be on the public
# internet (use ngrok / smee / Cloudflare Tunnel for local dev).

# Required: signing key for better-auth (use a long random string in every environment).
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET="change-me-in-prod"
MAGIC_LINK_TTL_MIN="15"
API_ORIGIN="http://localhost:4002"
WEB_ORIGIN="http://localhost:4001"
WWW_ORIGIN="http://localhost:4000"
# Optional: comma-separated list of additional browser origins allowed by
# CORS and trusted by better-auth. Handy when running both frontend shells
# (TanStack Start on :4001 and Next.js on :4003) against one API.
ADDITIONAL_WEB_ORIGINS="http://localhost:4003"
PORT="4002"

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Transactional email
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In production, when RESEND_API_KEY is set, magic links and invites go
# through Resend. In local dev, the console mailer is used instead (links
# logged + exposed via GET /v1/dev/last-magic-link) unless you set:

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth providers
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave unset to disable a provider; better-auth only registers providers
# whose client id + secret are both set. Redirect URIs to register:
#   Google: ${API_ORIGIN}/v1/auth/callback/google
#   Apple:  ${API_ORIGIN}/v1/auth/callback/apple
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=""
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=""
# APPLE_CLIENT_ID=""
# APPLE_CLIENT_SECRET=""

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Billing
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BILLING_PROVIDER acts as the master switch: when unset or "noop", the
# /v1/workspaces/:slug/billing/* routes return a disabled-state response
# and no provider SDK is constructed. Set to one of "stripe" | "polar" |
# "dodo" to wire the matching adapter — each has its own secrets.
#
# Plans rendered on the billing settings page. Keep this small; when you
# outgrow a handful, replace the catalog source in `composition.ts`
# with a DB-backed provider instead of embedding it in env. For Polar /
# Dodo, `priceId` should be the provider's product id.

# Stripe — you're the merchant of record.

# Polar — merchant-of-record, indie-friendly. `POLAR_SERVER` defaults to
# "sandbox"; switch to "production" when you graduate to live keys.

# Dodo Payments — merchant-of-record, Stainless-generated SDK.
# `DODO_PAYMENTS_ENVIRONMENT` defaults to "test_mode"; switch to
# "live_mode" for production.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# File uploads (UploadThing)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave unset to disable signed-upload endpoints. Create a project at
# https://uploadthing.com and paste the token here to enable.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Waitlist mode
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When "true", the final step of /onboarding is replaced with a "you're on
# the waitlist" thank-you screen instead of creating a workspace. The
# POST /v1/waitlist endpoint accepts submissions regardless of this flag
# — it only gates the UI behavior.
# If set, `POST /v1/waitlist/accept` with `Authorization: Bearer <this>`
# can mark a `waitlist_entries` row as approved so that email may sign up.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Audit log retention
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Daily cron at 03:00 UTC deletes audit entries older than this many days.
# Default 90. Set to 0 (or any non-positive value) to keep the schedule
# registered but make the cleanup a no-op. The cron requires `JOBS_PROVIDER`
# to be configured — without a worker, nothing fires.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Webhook forwarding for local dev (smee.io)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Visit https://smee.io/new once, paste the URL here, then register it as
# your Stripe dashboard webhook endpoint. The apps/webhook-tunnel
# workspace reads SMEE_URL and forwards POSTs to the local API. Override
# the target path if you're building against another provider adapter.
